 A picture of a lone accident by an articulated vehicle crashed a building situated at Owode-Onirin of Lagos. Photo/NAN  Dr Olufemi Oke-Osanyintolu, the Director-General, Lagos State Emergency Management Agency (LASEMA) confirmed that the accident, saying it happened around 4.10 p.m. on Lagos-Ikorodu express. He said that a preliminary report on the accident inward Owode Onirin revealed that the empty articulated truck was involved in a lone accident. “The articulated truck veered off the road and crashed into a residential building at Owode-Onirin,’’ he told a correspondent of the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN). He, however, said that no injuries recorded as the driver and residents of the building were unhurt. A picture of a lone accident by an articulated vehicle crashed a building situated at Owode-Onirin of Lagos. Photo/NAN  He said that the truck had been recovered off the building with the aid of a private tow truck. He added that the incident had been handed over to the Police at Owode Onirin police station for further investigation.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .